	(258,1,'2016-07-05 20:32:51','2016-07-05 20:32:51','[:sr]<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 16px;\">Zent opstaje zahvaljujući velikodušnosti, solidarnosti i podršci svojih čitalaca. Ako možeš pretplati se, poruči, ili doniraj. </span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Zentu cilj nije profit već pristupačno znanje za sve. Zent je utemeljen u vrednostima zajedništva ali i uverenju da država i državljanstvo nisu njegov nužni medijator. Zent shvata zajedništvo kao prvi od preduslova za ostvarivanje izvan-rednog mesta za sve.</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Svojom donacijom podržaćete štampana i online izdanja časopisa, održavanje javnih razgovora i predavanja kao i rad kritičara/ki, teoretičara/ki, umetnika/ca, pisaca i spisateljica.</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><br /><br /></p>[:en]<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 16px;\">Zent survives thanks to the generosity, solidarity and support of its readers. If you can please subscribe, purchase, or donate.</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">Zent does not strive to profit but to offer accessible knowledge for all. Zent is grounded in the values of the common and the conviction that neither the state nor citizenship are its necessary mediators. Zent understands the existence of the common as the first prerequisite for achieving an extra-ordinary place for all.</span></p><p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\">With your donation you will support print and online editions of the magazine, organization of public discussions and lectures, as well as the work of independent authors: critics, theorists, artist, and writers.</span></p>[:]','Podrži','','inherit','closed','closed','','37-revision-v1','','','2016-07-05 20:32:51','2016-07-05 20:32:51','',37,'http://zentmagazine.com/test/37-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(259,1,'2016-07-05 20:44:23','2016-07-05 20:44:23','[:sr]<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">Zent je časopis za izvan-redno promišljanje sadašnjosti.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Zent je prekaran – neizvestan, rizičan, nepredvidljiv. U isto vreme ugrožen i nesiguran u samoga sebe. Intutivan pre nego programiran, nasumičan pre nego usidren, mesto za misao, praksu i izraz. Zent je forma anksioznosti, aktivna, svesna izmeštenost.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">U žargonu (srpsko-hrvatskog jezika) zentati se podrazumeva određeni nivo straha (od) i anksioznosti (prema). Upravo zbog toga Zent je mesto prelaznosti i podvođenja: umesto bežanja i negiranja, Zent iskorišćava Strah. Zentati se znači iščekivati (ništa određeno), biti izvan reda i izvan mesta, neprestano u ruševinama, na ničijoj zemlji, nikada tamo gde te se očekuje. Jer da bi se uzdrmao postojeći poredak potrebno je sakupiti zajedničke snage, odupreti se svakom pokušaju aproprijacije, naturalizacije i normalizacije.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Zent je prostor za artikulisano političko mišljenje koje nije demagoško, konformističko i banalno. Ipak, Zent je mesto i za spontanost, patetiku i grešku. Zent je političan utoliko što politiku ne vidi samo kao pitanje institucija već pre svega kao pitanje svakodnevnog odnosa pojedinaca i zajednica jednih prema drugima i prema svetu. Zent je (samo)kritičan i polemičan. Zent postoji u formi tematskih štampanih izdanja i online časopisa koji redovno objavljuje eseje, intervjue, recenzije, poeziju, prozu i vizualne radove. Zent piše smelim, pristupačnim jezikom i eksperimentiše sa formama izraza, sa namerom da problematizuje odnos između ‘visoke’, ‘narodne’ i ‘popularne’ kulture, ‘eksperata’ i ‘amatera’, upravitelja i onih kojima se upravlja.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Tekstove objavljene na Zentu možete slobodno kopirati i prenositi uz obavezno jasno istaknuto ime autora/ke i izvor članka kao i uz uslov da ga potom sami ne zaštićujete autorskim pravom.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p>[:en]<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400; font-size: 20px;\">Zent is a magazine for extra-ordinary reflections on the present.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Zent is a precarious – uncertain, risky, unpredictable. Both unsafe and insecure. Intuitive rather than programmed, adrift rather than anchored, a place for thought, practice and expression. Zent is a form of anxiety. An active, conscious displacement.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">In vernacular Serbo-Croatian language to zent implies a certain degree of fear (from) and anxiety (for). Precisely because of that Zent is a transitive and subsuming place: instead of fleeing and negating, Zent exploits the fear. To zent is to anticipate (nothing in particular), to be out-of- order and out-of-place, constantly in ruins, in no man’s land, never there where you are expected. For to shake established orders is to accumulate collective strengths, resisting any attempts at appropriation, naturalization and normalization.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Zent is a place for articulated political opinion that is not conformist and banal. However, Zent is also a space for spontaneity, pathos and mistakes. Zent is political, insofar as it doesn’t see politics only as an institutional matter, but rather as a question of everyday relationships of individuals and communities between each other and the world. Zent is (self)critical and polemical. Zent takes the form of periodical tematic printed editions and online magazine that regularly publishes essays, interviews, reviews, poetry, fiction and visual works. Zent writes in bold, accessible language and experiments with the forms of expression, with intention to question the relationship between ‘high’, ‘folk’ and ‘popular’ culture, ‘experts’ and ‘amateurs’, governors and those who are to be governed.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\">Articles published on Zent can be freely copied and shared but with clearly stated name of the author and source of the article as well as under the condition that you do not protect the article with copyright.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p>[:]','[:sr]O nama[:en]About Us[:]','','inherit','closed','closed','','28-revision-v1','','','2016-07-05 20:44:23','2016-07-05 20:44:23','',28,'http://zentmagazine.com/test/28-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
